(85, 2, '2011-08-27 21:48:00', '2011-08-27 21:48:00', '<div><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-9pYuQ86Ftws/TllkMnTEt-I/AAAAAAAAA7M/0WfxOJm4xLI/s1600/IMG_4452.JPG" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="400" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-9pYuQ86Ftws/TllkMnTEt-I/AAAAAAAAA7M/0WfxOJm4xLI/s400/IMG_4452.JPG" width="312"></a></div><div><br></div><div>One year ago the Paws & Effect Military Litter began a journey to being great service dogs. They have all grown up and they are learning the ways of working. We celebrated their first birthday by hosting a party at the Gold Star Museum at Camp Dodge, Iowa. We had nearly all the service dogs present for the unveiling of the all new public service announcements and the 6 minute puppy raiser documentary. </div><div><br></div><div>Paws & Effect was also surprised with a $2,000.00 donation from the <a href="http://integer.com/">Integer Group</a> in Denver. During their performance party this year they auctioned off t-shirts to raise money for Paws & Effect. We truly appreciate the thoughts and the donation, it will be used wisely. And we truly were shocked to see someone from Denver show up at the party with a HUGE check.</div><div><br></div><div>Thank you to one and all!</div><div><br></div><div>All puppy raisers got a piece of the cake. </div><br><div><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-3A7EwgkU9Es/TllkNFqoniI/AAAAAAAAA7U/XVynmTAyhNQ/s1600/IMG_4451.JPG" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="269" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-3A7EwgkU9Es/TllkNFqoniI/AAAAAAAAA7U/XVynmTAyhNQ/s400/IMG_4451.JPG" width="400"></a></div><div><br></div><div><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-CDmMfKZ3N9s/TllmJV3kfrI/AAAAAAAAA7g/oF7YAaGxAH8/s1600/IMG_4391.JPG" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="259" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-CDmMfKZ3N9s/TllmJV3kfrI/AAAAAAAAA7g/oF7YAaGxAH8/s320/IMG_4391.JPG" width="320"></a></div><br><div><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-Ay2uyN6nLvY/TllkNQOC1xI/AAAAAAAAA7c/MgfUsl7S3ew/s1600/IMG_4450.JPG" imageanchor="1"><img 