(112, 2, '2011-04-20 17:44:00', '2011-04-20 17:44:00', '<div><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-ljsUHd-63jo/Ta8bTdL_hcI/AAAAAAAAA3Y/BUijIiXH8CU/s1600/IMG00061-20110420-0928.jpg" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="240" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-ljsUHd-63jo/Ta8bTdL_hcI/AAAAAAAAA3Y/BUijIiXH8CU/s320/IMG00061-20110420-0928.jpg" width="320"></a></div>', 'MG Orr welcomes Ryder to Joint Force Headquarters', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'mg-orr-welcomes-ryder-to-joint-force-headquarters', '', '', '2011-04-20 17:44:00', '2011-04-20 17:44:00', '', 0, 'http://www.dev.paws-effect.org/wp/2011/04/mg-orr-welcomes-ryder-to-joint-force-headquarters.html', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(113, 2, '2011-04-18 04:04:00', '2011-04-18 04:04:00', 'Liberty, one of the service puppies from the military litter, got several opportunities to \'do the town\' this weekend. Her performance was exemplary in every one of the public settings.<br><br><div><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-ycDAztLMfqE/Tau2ZGRT91I/AAAAAAAAA3U/UVuGx4JyNuc/s1600/LibertyKernnel.jpg" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="320" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-ycDAztLMfqE/Tau2ZGRT91I/AAAAAAAAA3U/UVuGx4JyNuc/s320/LibertyKernnel.jpg" width="240"></a></div><b><span><br></span></b><br><b>Liberty and the Kernel.</b><br>It should be no surprise that the floors of many restaurants have morsels of goodness sprinkled and spread throughout. As was the case this morning when Liberty spotted a single kernel of corn that was left over from a previous patron but Liberty did the right thing and kept her distance.<br><br><div><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-8Q3fo0oI9Es/Tau1G8wLg5I/AAAAAAAAA3M/1bu6Swl6LEk/s1600/photo-10.JPG" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="320" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-8Q3fo0oI9Es/Tau1G8wLg5I/AAAAAAAAA3M/1bu6Swl6LEk/s320/photo-10.JPG" width="240"></a></div><div><br></div><div>Shortly there after she was on her side dreaming of great days ahead.</div><div><br></div><div><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-TwfrcOJmchc/Tau1Jw84vCI/AAAAAAAAA3Q/HmWOoiVDbT0/s1600/photo-7.JPG" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="320" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-TwfrcOJmchc/Tau1Jw84vCI/AAAAAAAAA3Q/HmWOoiVDbT0/s320/photo-7.JPG" width="240"></a></div><br>After a long morning of work Liberty was rewarded to an afternoon in the backyard playing with all the pet dogs.<br><br>Now that\'s a dogs life.<br><br>We all know deep inside she was \'willing\' that kernel to come to her but that wasn\'t going to work out that way. This experience shows that she\'s has been exposed to similar situations and her restraint proves that she\'s on track to be a great service dog.', 'Liberty and the Kernel.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'liberty-and-the-kernel', '', '', '2011-04-18 04:04:00', '2011-04-18 04:04:00', '', 0, 'http://www.dev.paws-effect.org/wp/2011/04/liberty-and-the-kernel.html', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(114, 2, '2011-04-14 19:01:00', '2011-04-14 19:01:00', '<div><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-SPVUT6TYQ0Q/TadD7XsO1BI/AAAAAAAAA3E/VNfOc1fDxz8/s1600/P%2526E+001.JPG" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="213" r6="true" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-SPVUT6TYQ0Q/TadD7XsO1BI/AAAAAAAAA3E/VNfOc1fDxz8/s320/P%2526E+001.JPG" width="320"></a></div><div><br></div><div>Here at Canine Craze, we are nearly set!  We\'re bringing both the Military Litter and the Red Bull Litter together for a proper send off as the new ones go to their puppy raisers.  We\'ve got food, toys, crates...all we\'re missing is....PUPPIES!﻿</div>', 'Who\'s Ready for the Red Bulls?!?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'whos-ready-for-the-red-bulls', '', '', '2011-04-14 19:01:00', '2011-04-14 19:01:00', '', 0, 'http://www.dev.paws-effect.org/wp/2011/04/whos-ready-for-the-red-bulls.html', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(115, 2, '2011-04-13 18:17:00', '2011-04-13 18:17:00', '<div><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-hRWoIhVDFro/TaXoHyA7Z6I/AAAAAAAAA3A/LT3qHbKacmg/s1600/Valor+%253A+Enable.png" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="168" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-hRWoIhVDFro/TaXoHyA7Z6I/AAAAAAAAA3A/LT3qHbKacmg/s320/Valor+%253A+Enable.png" width="320"></a></div><br>A huge THANK YOU to Cedar Rapids VALOR and EnAble for their support and donations.  The $5,500 they raised offset the cost of acquiring the five puppies in the Red Bull Litter, purchasing health insurance, dog food, toys and all the extras that come along with the new additions.', 'Thank you PepsiCo and Quaker!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'thank-you-pepsico-and-quaker', '', '', '2011-04-13 18:17:00', '2011-04-13 18:17:00', '', 0, 'http://www.dev.paws-effect.org/wp/2011/04/thank-you-pepsico-and-quaker.html', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(116, 2, '2011-04-13 03:01:00', '2011-04-13 03:01:00', '<div><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-ABI1cGceRtE/TaUQHHbAKmI/AAAAAAAAA20/oyEezstFp3g/s1600/photo%25289%2529.JPG" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="240" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-ABI1cGceRtE/TaUQHHbAKmI/AAAAAAAAA20/oyEezstFp3g/s320/photo%25289%2529.JPG" width="320"></a></div>Paws & Effect took home a PRIME Award for our "We Serve with Honor" campaign. <a href="http://prsaciowa.org/">PRSA</a> (Public Relations Society of America) hosts the prime awards every year to celebrate the best PR and corporate communications work in the community.<br><br><br><div><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-XKLCYpdv2oQ/TaUQIKYyatI/AAAAAAAAA24/MdZYWgOBies/s1600/photo%252810%2529.JPG" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="200" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-XKLCYpdv2oQ/TaUQIKYyatI/AAAAAAAAA24/MdZYWgOBies/s200/photo%252810%2529.JPG" width="150"></a><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-T4hyr_daZV0/TaUQKu-Nr9I/AAAAAAAAA28/A7Dy6GFEChg/s1600/photo%252811%2529.JPG" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="200" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-T4hyr_daZV0/TaUQKu-Nr9I/AAAAAAAAA28/A7Dy6GFEChg/s200/photo%252811%2529.JPG" width="150"></a></div><br>Not to be out done by our winning an award, 9 week old Archer stole the show. However he quickly became a 15 pound sack of potatoes and fell fast asleep by the end of the presentation. Tonight was Archers\' first public appearance and he enjoyed wearing his <a href="http://propper.com/">Propper</a> MultiCam (camouflage) service dog vest.<br><br>What a great night for Paws & Effect and for all our volunteers and supporters.<br><br>We know what it takes to make a difference.', 'Guess who won a 2011 PRIME Award?!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'guess-who-won-a-2011-prime-award', '', '', '2011-04-13 03:01:00', '2011-04-13 03:01:00', '', 0, 'http://www.dev.paws-effect.org/wp/2011/04/guess-who-won-a-2011-prime-award.html', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(117, 2, '2011-04-12 12:03:00', '2011-04-12 12:03:00', '<div><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-wfaLbwzuz4I/TaQ_hp8nBnI/AAAAAAAAA2s/oipf8vIjs2o/s1600/Pentagon+Channel.png" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="239" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-wfaLbwzuz4I/TaQ_hp8nBnI/AAAAAAAAA2s/oipf8vIjs2o/s320/Pentagon+Channel.png" width="320"></a></div><br><div><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-gsPhzV7Ej9c/TaQ_la7ja0I/AAAAAAAAA2w/uh--r_f-Ehs/s1600/Picture+1.png" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="238" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-gsPhzV7Ej9c/TaQ_la7ja0I/AAAAAAAAA2w/uh--r_f-Ehs/s320/Picture+1.png" width="320"></a></div>', 'Hooah, Paws & Effect!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'hooah-paws-effect', '', '', '2011-04-12 12:03:00', '2011-04-12 12:03:00', '', 0, 'http://www.dev.paws-effect.org/wp/2011/04/hooah-paws-effect.html', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(118, 2, '2011-04-09 00:45:00', '2011-04-09 00:45:00', '<div><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-XTMu4rK2yGI/TZ-ryOeC3OI/AAAAAAAAA2o/aoU_h6ys1q4/s1600/Steven+and+Fi.jpg" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="320" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-XTMu4rK2yGI/TZ-ryOeC3OI/AAAAAAAAA2o/aoU_h6ys1q4/s320/Steven+and+Fi.jpg" width="240"></a></div><br>After a few days at Camp Dodge learning a bit more about dog training and public access, Fi was placed with combat veteran Steven.  Looks like they are off to a great start!', 'Fiyero has been placed!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'fiyero-has-been-placed', '', '', '2011-04-09 00:45:00', '2011-04-09 00:45:00', '', 0, 'http://www.dev.paws-effect.org/wp/2011/04/fiyero-has-been-placed.html', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(119, 2, '2011-04-04 17:17:00', '2011-04-04 17:17:00', '<table align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tbody><tr><td><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-75qH9JO7JLE/TZn72f48c-I/AAAAAAAAA2g/dch81PdxnUk/s1600/CC_110402_FamilySeries.jpg" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="265" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-75qH9JO7JLE/TZn72f48c-I/AAAAAAAAA2g/dch81PdxnUk/s400/CC_110402_FamilySeries.jpg" width="400"></a></td></tr><tr><td>Photo by Dani Ausen</td></tr></tbody></table><div></div><br><br><div>Paws & Effect joined in the fun of discovery at the <a href="http://www.civiccenter.org/willis_broadway_series/family_series.php">Civic Center of Greater Des Moines\' Family Series</a> event on Saturday April 2.</div><div><div><br></div></div><div><div>The kids and parents alike got to interact with the dogs at one of the discovery stations. As you can see in the photo one of the Pet Partners, Michelle Walker and Lizzie, connected with the kids. </div><div><br></div><div><b>There is nothing like having a dog smile back!</b></div></div><div><div><br></div></div><div><div>We are so privileged to have such innovative opportunities in the community to make a difference. Thank You to the Civic Center for hosting another one of Des Moines best family events ever and for inviting Paws & Effect to take part.  </div><div><div><div><br></div></div></div></div>', 'Darwin the Dinosaur is more than just a dinosaur.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'darwin-the-dinosaur-is-more-than-just-a-dinosaur', '', '', '2011-04-04 17:17:00', '2011-04-04 17:17:00', '', 0, 'http://www.dev.paws-effect.org/wp/2011/04/darwin-the-dinosaur-is-more-than-just-a-dinosaur.html', 0, 'post', '', 2),
(120, 2, '2011-04-04 02:59:00', '2011-04-04 02:59:00', '<div><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-SvrKbW4DKkY/TZkzrv8VnrI/AAAAAAAAA2c/9a12GFnOW54/s1600/Archer.jpg" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="400" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-SvrKbW4DKkY/TZkzrv8VnrI/AAAAAAAAA2c/9a12GFnOW54/s400/Archer.jpg" width="263"></a></div><br>We welcome the first installment of Paws & Effect\'s Red Bull litter. His name is Archer.<br><br>The second military litter of service puppies will be named to honor Iowa National Guard\'s 34th Infantry "Red Bull" Division.<br><br>Each puppy will have a designation (name) assigned that matches the Red Bull\'s call signals.<br><br><a href="http://www.redbullrising.com/">Read more about the Red Bull division.</a>', 'Archer', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'archer', '', '', '2011-04-04 02:59:00', '2011-04-04 02:59:00', '', 0, 'http://www.dev.paws-effect.org/wp/2011/04/archer.html', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(121, 2, '2011-04-02 01:14:00', '2011-04-02 01:14:00', '<div><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-7xHX2liFcH0/TZYE7JNLR-I/AAAAAAAAA2U/idD8RKgv_HU/s1600/IMG_0857.JPG" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="400" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-7xHX2liFcH0/TZYE7JNLR-I/AAAAAAAAA2U/idD8RKgv_HU/s400/IMG_0857.JPG" width="300"></a></div><br>Paws & Effect was celebrated at a fundraiser held at Sticks last night. We are extremely pleased to have so many attend and support our cause.<br><br>A special <b>Thank You</b> goes to <b>Becky Beach and Jeff Lamberti</b> for believing in the program and putting together a wonderful event.<br><br>We must also thank all the volunteers and the countless hours that it took to seam all the pieces together and to <b><a href="http://www.sticks.com/">Sticks</a></b> for creating the original art and providing part of the proceeds of the dog themed items.<br><br>We are truly impressed by the support extended for a program we so deeply believe in:  the placement of service dogs  to support our Iowa National Guard troops upon return from deployment.<br><br><div><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-lXXNO1Ik-kc/TZYE8s2Up_I/AAAAAAAAA2Y/WC0bgzr_Tdo/s1600/IMG_0838.jpg" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="400" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-lXXNO1Ik-kc/TZYE8s2Up_I/AAAAAAAAA2Y/WC0bgzr_Tdo/s400/IMG_0838.jpg" width="300"></a></div>', 'Fundraiser at Sticks', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'fundraiser-at-sticks', '', '', '2011-04-02 01:14:00', '2011-04-02 01:14:00', '', 0, 'http://www.dev.paws-effect.org/wp/2011/04/fundraiser-at-sticks.html', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(122, 2, '2011-03-31 15:37:00', '2011-03-31 15:37:00', '<table align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tbody><tr><td><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-W8RB2idITk4/TZSd7aOcxyI/AAAAAAAAA2Q/vbX9nkLA5sw/s1600/BR-40U40.jpg" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="242" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-W8RB2idITk4/TZSd7aOcxyI/AAAAAAAAA2Q/vbX9nkLA5sw/s400/BR-40U40.jpg" width="400"></a></td></tr><tr><td>"Everyone loves puppies" - Nicole describing the photograph projected.</td></tr></tbody></table><br>Congratulations to Nicole Shumate on your winning the Business Records "Forty Under 40" Award.<br><br>"Central Iowa’s future is in good hands, as you’ll see when you read about the members of the Business Record’s “Forty Under 40” class for 2011. The young honorees have put together remarkable resumes, filled with professional success and civic contributions, and we’re proud to recognize their achievements."', 'Congratulations Nicole.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'congratulations-nicole', '', '', '2011-03-31 15:37:00', '2011-03-31 15:37:00', '', 0, 'http://www.dev.paws-effect.org/wp/2011/03/congratulations-nicole.html', 0, 'post', '', 0),
