(124, 2, '2011-03-30 16:56:00', '2011-03-30 16:56:00', '<table align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tbody><tr><td><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-PdkM5s5mLrc/TZNcn5LJ4eI/AAAAAAAAA2A/fn65pPY2v10/s1600/Presentation.jpg" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="313" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-PdkM5s5mLrc/TZNcn5LJ4eI/AAAAAAAAA2A/fn65pPY2v10/s320/Presentation.jpg" width="320"></a></td></tr><tr><td><span><span><span>Todd Cerveris - Producer/Director<br>Nicole Shumate - Executive Director of Paws & Effect<br>Renee Jetter presented stories from behind the scenes.</span></span></span></td></tr></tbody></table>Paws & Effect brought together the cast, crew and supporters to formally launch our public service announcements.<br><br>Four days of filming, several weeks of post production including modifying the scripts, editing, voice overs and composing the background music (not to mention the several hundred volunteered man hours that went into producing the 5 TV spots) resulted in 2 1/2 minutes of airtime.<br><br><table align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tbody><tr><td><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-1NcltmzD8rE/TZNckQzvhHI/AAAAAAAAA14/oO7zROislCU/s1600/Roggen-Star.png" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="320" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-1NcltmzD8rE/TZNckQzvhHI/AAAAAAAAA14/oO7zROislCU/s320/Roggen-Star.png" width="253"></a></td></tr><tr><td>Roggen-Grind - One of the \'dog stars\' of the PSA was <br>on hand to receive the Regional Silver ADDY award.</td></tr></tbody></table><br>During the launch party it was announced, to our surprise, that our work not only won a Gold ADDY award for advertising and a Top Ten Overall at the local level but we also won a Regional Silver ADDY(R) award.  The spots now move on to national competition!<br><br>We can\'t express enough how proud we are of our volunteers, the cast and crew for the PSAs but also for the Iowa soldiers that serve our country with selfless pride and honor that provided the backdrop for message.<br><br><table align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tbody><tr><td><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-gbLauzckZt0/TZNcmtxR77I/AAAAAAAAA18/oJQtj65hIZA/s1600/Cake.jpg" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="400" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-gbLauzckZt0/TZNcmtxR77I/AAAAAAAAA18/oJQtj65hIZA/s400/Cake.jpg" width="256"></a></td></tr><tr><td>Congratulations to Paws & Effect.</td></tr></tbody></table><br>Thanks to everyone.', 'A GOLD Star and Silver Award Event', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-gold-star-and-silver-award-event', '', '', '2011-03-30 16:56:00', '2011-03-30 16:56:00', '', 0, 'http://www.dev.paws-effect.org/wp/2011/03/a-gold-star-and-silver-award-event.html', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(125, 2, '2011-03-29 14:09:00', '2011-03-29 14:09:00', '<div><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-1cpdfFfCTus/TZHnNWD6nTI/AAAAAAAAA10/v8XiOwVx-LY/s1600/Aprils+Fool.png" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="286" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-1cpdfFfCTus/TZHnNWD6nTI/AAAAAAAAA10/v8XiOwVx-LY/s400/Aprils+Fool.png" width="400"></a></div><br>Paws & Effect\'s April Fool Fun Run Premium has been posted. Join us Sunday April 16, 2011 for a fun-filled day of obstacles.<br><br><a href="http://paws-effect.org/Media/PNE%20Agility%20Fun%20Match%20May2011.doc">Click here for a Word document with the details.</a><br><br><a href="http://paws-effect.org/Media/PNE%20Agility%20Fun%20Match%20May2011.pdf">Click here for a PDF with the details.</a>', 'April Fools Fun Run', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'april-fools-fun-run', '', '', '2011-03-29 14:09:00', '2011-03-29 14:09:00', '', 0, 'http://www.dev.paws-effect.org/wp/2011/03/april-fools-fun-run.html', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(126, 2, '2011-03-24 22:47:00', '2011-03-24 22:47:00', '<div><a href="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-oSUQPUcPJ9s/TYvJQ69Bf3I/AAAAAAAAA1w/2CkFa7_yH9c/s1600/get_entry.jpeg.png" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="240" src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-oSUQPUcPJ9s/TYvJQ69Bf3I/AAAAAAAAA1w/2CkFa7_yH9c/s320/get_entry.jpeg.png" width="320"></a></div><br>Bissell hosts an online competition by which the winning contestant can direct a donation to their favorite charity.  Please vote for Paws & Effect Moose daily this week by registering <a href="http://bissell.promo.eprize.com/mvpcontest/registration.html?dest=vote">here</a>, and then searching for:<br><br><span></span><br><h3>Moose</h3><div>Pet Parent: Steve H.    Entrant #: 128712</div><div><br></div>', 'Vote For Paws & Effect Moose', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'vote-for-paws-effect-moose', '', '', '2011-03-24 22:47:00', '2011-03-24 22:47:00', '', 0, 'http://www.dev.paws-effect.org/wp/2011/03/vote-for-paws-effect-moose.html', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(127, 2, '2011-03-24 10:12:00', '2011-03-24 10:12:00', 'Here\'s what they said about her in the Business Record\'s 40 Under Forty article that recognizes 2011\'s Honorees:<br><br><div><a href="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-stidcFSitdg/TYsY3muYlkI/AAAAAAAAA1s/gFvrx3p6WkU/s1600/Nicole-Eric.jpg" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-stidcFSitdg/TYsY3muYlkI/AAAAAAAAA1s/gFvrx3p6WkU/s1600/Nicole-Eric.jpg"></a></div><strong>Age 38  |  Executive director, Paws & Effect</strong><br><br>Nicole Shumate came to Iowa from Colorado to get a law degree from Drake University, but ended up following another passion.<br><br>Shumate runs a nonprofit company called Paws & Effect, which trains therapy and service dogs and places them with people who need them. Right now, the organization is focused on placing dogs with combat veterans in Iowa who have disabilities or who have been diagnosed with post-traumatic stress disorder.<br><br>“Dog training has always been an interest of mine,” said Shumate, who used to raise and train dogs in Colorado. “As far as placing dogs with combat veterans, I just felt like it was our role in the community to really meet that purpose, having so many soldiers deployed right now.”<br><br>Shumate founded the organization in 2006, and said she kept it under the radar while going through law school, where she earned a degree in 2009. She decided to continue with dog training rather than go into practicing law.<br><br>“It was just a good education to have,” she said, noting that she’s able to utilize it in her role as executive director.<br><br>Her mission to help soldiers caught the attention of her mentor, Iowa Army National Guard Maj. Amy Price.<br><br>“Just the passion and drive that she’s given to this passion of hers – I’ve never seen a nonprofit organization do so many things for soldiers,” Price said.<br><br>Shumate also uses her organization to help out with ChildServe, a nonprofit that provides services to families with children who have special health-care needs. Through that, she works with a child to meet once a week and complete a dog agility course.<br><br>Shumate is also a team leader in critical incident stress management (CISM) debriefing for the Iowa Disaster Behavioral Health Response Team and is a CISM facilitator for the Federal Emergency Management Agency in Iowa.<br><br>She has been involved with Orchard Place as a member of the pet therapy team, and worked with a number of pet nonprofit programs in Colorado before moving to Des Moines.<br><br>Price said: “We teach our soldiers about Army values with the acronym LDRSHIP – loyalty, duty, respect for others, honor, integrity, personal courage – she just encompasses all of those values.”<span><br></span>', 'Congratulations to our executive director!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'congratulations-to-our-executive-director', '', '', '2011-03-24 10:12:00', '2011-03-24 10:12:00', '', 0, 'http://www.dev.paws-effect.org/wp/2011/03/congratulations-to-our-executive-director.html', 0, 'post', '', 2),
(128, 2, '2011-03-20 18:34:00', '2011-03-20 18:34:00', '<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tbody><tr><td><a href="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-xrlPKji2ujc/TYZHCheXxGI/AAAAAAAAA1k/G24YteBdkCI/s1600/IMG_0750.jpg" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="400" src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-xrlPKji2ujc/TYZHCheXxGI/AAAAAAAAA1k/G24YteBdkCI/s400/IMG_0750.jpg" width="300"></a></td></tr></tbody></table><div><a href="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-Qu-1wzAsYro/TYZHDKqcZ2I/AAAAAAAAA1o/eeARcpCBPoA/s1600/IMG_0752.jpg" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="400" src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-Qu-1wzAsYro/TYZHDKqcZ2I/AAAAAAAAA1o/eeARcpCBPoA/s400/IMG_0752.jpg" width="300"></a><a href="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-Qu-1wzAsYro/TYZHDKqcZ2I/AAAAAAAAA1o/eeARcpCBPoA/s1600/IMG_0752.jpg" imageanchor="1"><span>It is next to normal to see Paws & Effect service dogs attending a performance at the Civic Center of Greater Des Moines. They were incredibly well mannered and chimed in during a well timed moment of the musical Next to Normal.</span></a><a href="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-Qu-1wzAsYro/TYZHDKqcZ2I/AAAAAAAAA1o/eeARcpCBPoA/s1600/IMG_0752.jpg" imageanchor="1"><br></a><a href="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-Qu-1wzAsYro/TYZHDKqcZ2I/AAAAAAAAA1o/eeARcpCBPoA/s1600/IMG_0752.jpg" imageanchor="1"><br></a></div>', 'Next to Normal.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'next-to-normal', '', '', '2011-03-20 18:34:00', '2011-03-20 18:34:00', '', 0, 'http://www.dev.paws-effect.org/wp/2011/03/next-to-normal.html', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(129, 2, '2011-03-16 01:50:00', '2011-03-16 01:50:00', '<div><a href="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-zzWYiJydp4Y/TYAXfO4-s3I/AAAAAAAAA1g/92Y7xpDsAM8/s1600/SAM_0135_0E3E89EB94EC9.jpg" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-zzWYiJydp4Y/TYAXfO4-s3I/AAAAAAAAA1g/92Y7xpDsAM8/s1600/SAM_0135_0E3E89EB94EC9.jpg"></a></div>Each month Whitfield & Eddy selects a community organization to  support for its "Casual for a Cause" day (a casual dress day for a  donation).  In February, <b><i>Paws & Effect</i></b>, a  non-profit organization based in Des Moines, was chosen.  This  organization raises, trains and places service dogs and therapy dogs for  the disabled and for disabled returning veterans.  There is no charge  to the disabled to receive a dog.  <b><i>Paws & Effect</i></b> relies almost entirely on community donations.<br>This is an organization which is close to us since member Megan Antenucci\'s spouse now has a service dog through <b><i>Paws & Effect</i></b>. <br>Through the generous donations of our members and employees at Whitfield, we contributed over $1200 to this very worthy cause.<br><br><a href="http://www.whitfieldlaw.com/news/view.cfm?newsid=84">Whitfield & Eddy </a>', 'Whitfield & Eddy gives to Paws & Effect', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'whitfield-eddy-gives-to-paws-effect', '', '', '2011-03-16 01:50:00', '2011-03-16 01:50:00', '', 0, 'http://www.dev.paws-effect.org/wp/2011/03/whitfield-eddy-gives-to-paws-effect.html', 0, 'post', '', 0),
