(224, 2, '2010-04-03 22:06:00', '2010-04-03 22:06:00', '<a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_8M0BX0lsHes/S7e9kDybIMI/AAAAAAAAAnU/UYJipcGuZCY/s1600/Airport-Crew.png"><img src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_8M0BX0lsHes/S7e9kDybIMI/AAAAAAAAAnU/UYJipcGuZCY/s400/Airport-Crew.png" alt="" border="0"></a><br>The Paws & Effect service dogs took to the skies in an effort to learn all that they can learn. We actually only took to the plane that was parked on the tarmac. The dogs took in the sounds, smells, textures, noises, sights and a whole lot more of traveling through the airport, through security screening, up and down escalators and elevators, stairs and ultimately up and into a plane.<br><br>But that\'s not all. They also figured out how to lure the flight crew into giving us all cookies! OK, so only the handlers got the fresh baked cookies that they whipped up at 26,000 feet but the dogs had their treats too.<br><br>The training session was a success. Congratulations Tag, Keeper, Gabor, Fyero, and Czar. You all did spectacularly!<br><br>Thank you to Air Midwest for providing us the plane and all the accommodations.', 'Airport Crew!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'airport-crew', '', '', '2010-04-03 22:06:00', '2010-04-03 22:06:00', '', 0, 'http://www.dev.paws-effect.org/wp/2010/04/airport-crew.html', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(225, 2, '2010-04-03 21:54:00', '2010-04-03 21:54:00', '<a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_8M0BX0lsHes/S7e6pRsxdaI/AAAAAAAAAm8/XJPIlYoM2F8/s1600/Family-Series-Civic-Center-1.png"><img src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_8M0BX0lsHes/S7e6pRsxdaI/AAAAAAAAAm8/XJPIlYoM2F8/s400/Family-Series-Civic-Center-1.png" alt="" border="0"></a>Another journey to the Civic Center of Greater Des Moines, this time it held their Family Series - Eric Carle\'s "The Very Hungry Caterpillar" discovery party and live performance. Six of our Pet Partner teams participated in the reading event. The chaos of 1,700 people was controlled to a dull roar. The kids loved the stories of Eric Carle and lapped up the dogs that were there.<br><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_8M0BX0lsHes/S7e6pk5mhXI/AAAAAAAAAnE/M7vee-0x9N4/s1600/Family-Series-Civic-Center2.png"><img src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_8M0BX0lsHes/S7e6pk5mhXI/AAAAAAAAAnE/M7vee-0x9N4/s400/Family-Series-Civic-Center2.png" alt="" border="0"></a>Another fun filled event. After the discovery was over several of the dog teams attended the live performance of The Hungry Caterpillar performed by the Mermaid Theatre of Nova Scotia under black light.<br><br>Bravo to part two of the Civic Centers Family Series. Looking forward to the next one now.<a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_8M0BX0lsHes/S7e6qG49EII/AAAAAAAAAnM/KVAk3GiAsyo/s1600/Family-Series-Civic-Center3.png"><img src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_8M0BX0lsHes/S7e6qG49EII/AAAAAAAAAnM/KVAk3GiAsyo/s400/Family-Series-Civic-Center3.png" alt="" border="0"></a>', 'Family Series - Eric Carle\'s "The Very Hungry Caterpillar"', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'family-series-eric-carles-the-very-hungry-caterpillar', '', '', '2010-04-03 21:54:00', '2010-04-03 21:54:00', '', 0, 'http://www.dev.paws-effect.org/wp/2010/04/family-series-eric-carles-the-very-hungry-caterpillar.html', 0, 'post', '', 0),
