(354, 2, '2008-05-05 16:35:00', '2008-05-05 16:35:00', '<a href="http://bp2.blogger.com/_8M0BX0lsHes/SB9kQ_HuqII/AAAAAAAAACs/h0IAdX9ptQA/s1600-h/Picture+2.png"><img src="http://bp2.blogger.com/_8M0BX0lsHes/SB9kQ_HuqII/AAAAAAAAACs/h0IAdX9ptQA/s320/Picture+2.png" alt="" border="0"></a><span><span><span><br><br>We were blown away with the success of Paws & Effects "Spring Fling" NADAC trial at Raccoon River Park this weekend.</span></span><span><br><br></span><span><span>High winds and cool temperatures only knocked the bars down on Saturday as everyone else, including the dogs braved the elements. Thanks to everyone who came out to play. We really appreciate the great distances traveled (Mississippi), the time spent and the fantastic handling skills of everyone playing this exciting game. Thank you!</span></span><span><br></span></span><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><span><span><br></span><span><span>Des Moines Register Article</span></span><span><br></span><a href="http://www.desmoinesregister.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=2008805040338"><span>http://www.desmoinesregister.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=2008805040338</span></a></span></div>', 'Blown away at the May Trial', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'blown-away-at-the-may-trial', '', '', '2008-05-05 16:35:00', '2008-05-05 16:35:00', '', 0, 'http://www.dev.paws-effect.org/wp/2008/05/blown-away-at-the-may-trial.html', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(355, 2, '2008-04-10 15:42:00', '2008-04-10 15:42:00', '<a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_8M0BX0lsHes/R_98cH9O9gI/AAAAAAAAACE/r8C0DXIfxEE/s1600-h/Roggen_11.19.jpg"><img src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_8M0BX0lsHes/R_98cH9O9gI/AAAAAAAAACE/r8C0DXIfxEE/s320/Roggen_11.19.jpg" border="0" alt=""></a><br>What would you do if you were confronted with these situations?<br><br>Setting: A retirement community sitting area.<br><br>During one of your visits you are surrounded by 6 or 7 individuals that are all enjoying the visit with your Pet Partner. Another individual approaches who is passionate about seeing the dog and on previous visits was the only one to take interest in the animal being in the facility. This individual feels that the others are taking away from them. The situation elevates and the individual start raising their voice and saying less then kind things about the other individuals in the room that are all having a pleasant time. The individual leaves the room and reenters a few moments later and is visibly angry.', 'Question: 01', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'question-01', '', '', '2008-04-10 15:42:00', '2008-04-10 15:42:00', '', 0, 'http://www.dev.paws-effect.org/wp/2008/04/question-01.html', 0, 'post', '', 2),
(356, 2, '2008-03-31 05:18:00', '2008-03-31 05:18:00', '<br><br>Had some really good runs come out of our first ever trial and our second ever fun run this weekend. Check out the premium for our May trial. We plan on continuing to make it bigger, bad \'er, and more fun in the future.', 'Teaser from our Inaugural Trial.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'teaser-from-our-inaugural-trial', '', '', '2008-03-31 05:18:00', '2008-03-31 05:18:00', '', 0, 'http://www.dev.paws-effect.org/wp/2008/03/teaser-from-our-inaugural-trial.html', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(357, 2, '2008-03-30 01:51:00', '2008-03-30 01:51:00', 'March Fun Run a complete success!<br>Seriously. Two firsts happened today. One of children at our ChildServer program showed up to compete today. Her run with Sofie was a wonderfully emotional time. Maddie did all she needed to do to complete the course with no time faults! This is really a cool thing if you knew that Maddie is in a motorized wheel chair. Maddie, my hats off to you, my heart goes out to you and you are my hero. Knowing what it takes to run your first run, the nerves, the thoughts that go through your mind before you get going. Wow. You did it and you showed us all that it can be done. Thanks for making my day. Yeah, I even had a tear in my eye and heart palpitations from all the positive excitement. Bummer your chair stopped working. <br><br>A less notable first was the Hoopers course that we ran today. It was introduced to NADAC this year and I have to say it is incredibly fun and todays run seemed to be sucessful. The sideline audience cheered on all the competitors. How cool. <br><br>Maddie, you stole the show and Hoopers are here to stay.', 'Two fantastic items to tell you about.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'two-fantastic-items-to-tell-you-about', '', '', '2008-03-30 01:51:00', '2008-03-30 01:51:00', '', 0, 'http://www.dev.paws-effect.org/wp/2008/03/two-fantastic-items-to-tell-you-about.html', 0, 'post', '', 3),
(358, 2, '2008-03-25 14:00:00', '2008-03-25 14:00:00', '<div><span><span>We had a great experience in filming this spot with ChildServe. As always the dogs brought smiles to the kids faces. </span></span></div>', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '358', '', '', '2008-03-25 14:00:00', '2008-03-25 14:00:00', '', 0, 'http://www.dev.paws-effect.org/wp/2008/03/358.html', 0, 'post', '', 1),
